Items.description: Carlos Beltran's three-run homer sparked a seven-run third inning and the St. Louis Cardinals got seven stingy innings from Adam Wainwright, delivering a reality jolt to the Pittsburgh Pirates with a 9-1 rout Thursday in their NL division series opener.
Items.title: NLDS 'A'
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Clayton Kershaw struck out 12 during seven dominant innings, Adrian Gonzalez hit a two-run homer and the Los Angeles Dodgers beat the bumbling Atlanta Braves 6-1 in Game 1 of the NL Division Series on Thursday night.
Items.title: NLDS 'B'
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Rookie Gerrit Cole gave up two hits in six dominant innings and drove in a run, Pedro Alvarez had a two-run homer, and the Pittsburgh Pirates beat the St. Louis Cardinals 7-1 Friday to even their division series at a game apiece.
Items.title: NLDS 'A'
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Jon Lester allowed three hits in 7 2/3 innings and the Boston Red Sox took advantage of poor Tampa Bay defense in a five-run fourth to beat the Rays 12-2 on Friday in Game 1 of the AL division series.
Items.title: ALDS 'A'
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: Mike Minor pitched six strong innings, Jason Heyward had a two-run single and the Atlanta Braves held on for a 4-3 victory over the Los Angeles Dodgers on Friday night, evening the NL division series at one game apiece.
Items.title: NLDS 'B'
Items.vs: Atlanta Braves vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Max Scherzer struck out 11 over seven dominant innings, Miguel Cabrera helped stake Detroit to an early lead before leaving in the eighth and the Tigers held on to beat the Oakland Athletics 3-2 on Friday night in the opener of their AL Division Series.
Items.title: ALDS 'B'
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: David Ortiz homered twice, the second shot chasing David Price in the eighth inning on Saturday night, and the Boston Red Sox beat the Tampa Bay Rays 7-4 to take a 2-0 lead in the AL division series.
Items.title: ALDS 'A'
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Tampa Bay Rays

Items.description: Stephen Vogt lined an RBI single in the ninth inning after rookie Sonny Gray matched zeros with Justin Verlander in a sensational playoff debut that helped the Athletics beat the Tigers 1-0 on Saturday night, tying their AL division series.
Items.title: ALDS 'B'
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: Pedro Alvarez hit a tiebreaking single in the eighth inning and the Pittsburgh Pirates beat the St. Louis Cardinals 5-3 on Sunday to take a 2-1 lead in best-of-five NL division series.
Items.title: NLDS 'A'
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Pirates vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Carl Crawford hit a three-run homer, Juan Uribe added a two-run shot and the Los Angeles Dodgers routed the Atlanta Braves 13-6 on Sunday night for a 2-1 lead in their best-of-five NL Division Series.
Items.title: NLDS 'B'
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Turns out the Oakland Athletics don't need a brilliant pitching performance to beat Detroit.
Items.title: ALDS 'B'
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Oakland Athletics

Items.description: Rookie Michael Wacha took a no-hit bid into the eighth inning and the St. Louis Cardinals showed off their October poise, edging the Pittsburgh Pirates 2-1 Monday and setting up a winner-take-all Game 5 in the NL division series.
Items.title: NLDS 'A'
Items.vs: Pittsburgh Pirates vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Jose Lobaton hit a solo home run with two outs in the bottom of the ninth inning, and the Tampa Bay Rays staved off elimination once again, beating the Boston Red Sox 5-4 on Monday night.
Items.title: ALDS 'A'
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Rays vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Juan Uribe hit a go-ahead, two-run homer in the eighth inning after Clayton Kershaw started on short rest for the Dodgers in a 4-3 victory over the Atlanta Braves on Monday night, sending Los Angeles into the National League Championship Series.
Items.title: NLDS 'B'
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Max Scherzer escaped a major jam in relief and the Detroit Tigers -- helped by two fans who reached out to reel in Victor Martinez's disputed home run -- rallied past the Oakland Athletics 8-6 on Tuesday to force a decisive fifth game in their AL Division
Items.title: ALDS 'B'
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Oakland Athletics

Items.description: Shane Victorino's infield single snapped a seventh-inning tie and journeyman Craig Breslow gave Boston a huge boost out of the bullpen, sending the Red Sox into the AL Championship Series with a 3-1 victory over the Tampa Bay Rays on Tuesday night.
Items.title: ALDS 'A'
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Rays vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Adam Wainwright pitched a complete game and the St. Louis Cardinals got two-run homers from David Freese and Matt Adams to beat the Pittsburgh Pirates 6-1 on Wednesday night and advance to the NL Championship Series.
Items.title: NLDS 'A'
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Pittsburgh Pirates

Items.description: Justin Verlander pitched another Game 5 gem in Oakland while carrying a no-hit bid into the seventh inning, and Miguel Cabrera homered to lead the Detroit Tigers past the Athletics 3-0 on Thursday night and back into the AL Championship Series.
Items.title: ALDS 'B'
Items.vs: Oakland Athletics vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: Carlos Beltran capped his latest scintillating postseason performance with an RBI single in the 13th inning early Saturday that lifted the St. Louis Cardinals over the Los Angeles Dodgers 3-2 in the NL Championship Series opener.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, NLCS, NLCS - GAME 1
Items.title: NLCS
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Rookie Michael Wacha pitched into the seventh inning with zero margin for error and the St. Louis Cardinals silenced the Los Angeles Dodgers for the second straight day, winning 1-0 Saturday for a 2-0 lead in the NL Championship Series.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, NLCS, NLCS - GAME 2
Items.title: NLCS
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Anibal Sanchez and four Detroit Tigers relievers came within two outs of the first combined no-hitter in postseason history, striking out 17 to beat the Boston Red Sox 1-0 Saturday night in the AL Championship Series Opener.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, ALCS, ALCS - GAME 1
Items.title: ALCS
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: David Ortiz revived the Red Sox with a tying grand slam in the eighth inning, then Jarrod Saltalamacchia hit a winning single in the ninth that sent Boston past the Detroit Tigers 6-5 Sunday night to even the AL Championship Series at 1-all.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, ALCS, ALCS - GAME 2
Items.title: ALCS
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: Hyun-Jin Ryu outpitched Adam Wainwright with seven innings of three-hit ball, and Los Angeles got back into the NL Championship Series with a 3-0 victory over the St. Louis Cardinals on Monday night.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, NLCS, NLCS - GAME 3
Items.title: NLCS
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: John Lackey edged Justin Verlander in the latest duel of these pitching-rich playoffs, and Boston's bullpen shut down Detroit's big boppers with the game on the line to lift the Red Sox over the Tigers 1-0 Tuesday for a 2-1 lead in the ALCS.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, ALCS, ALCS - GAME 3
Items.title: ALCS
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Matt Holliday and pinch hitter Shane Robinson hit the first home runs of the NL Championship Series, and the St. Louis Cardinals beat the Los Angeles Dodgers 4-2 on Tuesday night to take a 3-1 lead in the best-of-seven matchup.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, NLCS, NLCS - GAME 4
Items.title: NLCS
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Adrian Gonzalez homered twice and Zack Greinke gave the Los Angeles Dodgers the clutch performance they needed in a 6-4 victory over the Cardinals on Wednesday that trimmed St. Louis' lead to 3-2 in the NL championship series.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, NLCS, NLCS - GAME 5
Items.title: NLCS
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: A revitalized Austin Jackson delivered in manager Jim Leyland's revamped lineup as the Detroit Tigers built a big lead and held on this time, beating the Boston Red Sox 7-3 on Wednesday night to even the AL Championship Series at 2-all.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, ALCS, ALCS - GAME 4
Items.title: ALCS
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Mike Napoli's majestic homer began a rare early Boston breakthrough, Junichi Tazawa again bested Miguel Cabrera in a crucial spot and the Red Sox moved within one win of reaching the World Series by edging the Detroit Tigers 4-3 on Thursday night.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, ALCS, ALCS - GAME 5
Items.title: ALCS
Items.vs: Detroit Tigers vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Carlos Beltran and the Cardinals stunned Clayton Kershaw with a four-run third inning, and St. Louis advanced to its second World Series in three seasons by roughing up the Los Angeles Dodgers 9-0 in Game 6 of the NL Championship Series on Friday night.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, NLCS, NLCS - GAME 6
Items.title: NLCS
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: The Boston Red Sox are going back to the World Series for the third time in 10 seasons.
Items.notes: League Championship Series, ALCS, ALCS - GAME 6
Items.title: ALCS
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: Mike Napoli hit a three-run double right after the umps reversed a blown call, Jon Lester made an early lead stand up and the Red Sox romped past sloppy St. Louis 8-1 on Wednesday night for their ninth straight win in a World Series game.
Items.title: World Series
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Michael Wacha won again in October and the St. Louis Cardinals got just enough help from Boston, beating the Red Sox 4-2 on Thursday night to tie the World Series at a game apiece.
Items.title: World Series
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. St. Louis Cardinals

Items.description: Third baseman Will Middlebrooks tripped Allen Craig for a game-ending obstruction call on Jon Jay's ninth-inning grounder, giving the St. Louis Cardinals a bizarre 5-4 win over the Boston Red Sox on Saturday night and a 2-1 World Series lead.
Items.title: World Series
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Jonny Gomes hit a tiebreaking, three-run homer in the sixth inning and the Boston Red Sox rallied to beat the St. Louis Cardinals 4-2 Sunday night, tying the World Series at two games each.
Items.title: World Series
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Jon Lester smothered St. Louis, David Ross hit a tiebreaking RBI double in a two-run seventh inning and the Boston Red Sox beat the Cardinals 3-1 on Monday night to take a 3-2 World Series lead.
Items.title: World Series
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: David Ortiz and the Boston Red Sox, baseball's bearded wonders, capped their remarkable turnaround by beating the St. Louis Cardinals 6-1 in Game 6 on Wednesday night to win their third World Series championship in 10 seasons.
Items.title: World Series
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. St. Louis Cardinals
